The '''Johns Hopkins University''', commonly referred to as '''Johns Hopkins''', '''JHU''', or simply '''Hopkins''', is a [[private university|private]] research university located in [[Baltimore, Maryland|Baltimore]], [[Maryland]], United States. Johns Hopkins also maintains full-time campuses elsewhere in Maryland, Washington, D.C., Italy, China, and Singapore. It is one of fourteen founding members of the [[Association of American Universities]].
